- Bandage application: Appropriate tension control

Speed & Accuracy:
- Peak Speed: 5 m/s hand motion
- Positioning Accuracy: ±0.1 mm (static), ±1 mm (dynamic)
- Repeatability: ±0.05 mm
- Settling Time: < 100 ms for 10 cm move
```

VI. POWER SYSTEMS

6.1 Energy Storage & Generation

```
Primary Battery:
- Chemistry: Solid-state lithium-sulfur (Li-S)
- Capacity: 20 kWh
- Voltage: 400 V nominal
- Weight: 15 kg
- Energy Density: 400 Wh/kg
- Cycle Life: 5000 cycles to 80% capacity
- Charging: 0-100% in 30 minutes (fast charge), 2 hours (standard)

Secondary Energy Sources:
1. Wireless Charging:
   - Technology: Resonant inductive coupling
   - Power: 5 kW at 85% efficiency
   - Alignment: Automatic via 6G positioning

2. Energy Harvesting:
   - Solar: Flexible perovskite cells on back (200 W peak)
   - Kinetic: Piezoelectric in joints (50 W during walking)
   - Thermal: Thermoelectric from motor heat (20 W)

3. Emergency Power:
   - Type: Betavoltaic (nuclear) backup
   - Source: Tritium (63Ni alternative)
   - Power: 10 W continuous for 10 years
   - Use: Critical systems only during blackouts

Power Management:
- Peak Consumption: 5 kW (all systems active)
- Average Consumption: 500 W (idle monitoring)
- Standby: 10 W (sleep mode)
- Runtime: 40 hours (typical), 8 hours (high intensity)
```

6.2 Thermal Management

```
Cooling Systems:
1. Quantum Processor:
   - Type: Dilution refrigerator
   - Stages: 4 (300K → 4K → 1K → 100mK → 15mK)
   - Cooling Power: 1 W at 100 mK
   - Cooldown Time: 8 hours from room temperature

2. Classical Electronics:
   - Type: Two-phase liquid cooling
   - Coolant: Novec 7100 (dielectric fluid)
   - Heat Removal: 2 kW maximum
   - Noise: < 25 dB

3. Motors & Actuators:
   - Type: Liquid cooling with microchannels
   - Coolant: Water-glycol mixture
   - Temperature Control: ±1°C

Heat Distribution:
- Total Heat Output: 500 W average, 2 kW peak
- Redistribution: Phase change material for peak loads
- External: Can dissipate to environment via radiators
```

